        "description": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI (stiffness, yield force) change of less than 2% between medium and fine mesh densities. Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for primary QoIs."
      },
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted (coarse: ~85k elements, medium: ~220k elements, fine: ~580k elements). Stiffness QoI changed by 1.3% between medium and fine; yield force changed by 0.9%. GCI for stiffness = 0.8%, GCI for yield force = 0.6%, both well below 2% threshold. Discretization error at Gradation 3: formal GCI computed and reported."
