      },
      "rationale": "An independent FEA analyst reviewed the model setup, boundary conditions (fixed-fixed ASTM F1717 fixture replication), material property assignments (Ti-6Al-4V per ASTM F136), and contact pair definitions. Review checklist completed and archived. No use errors identified. Gradation 2 achieved: independent review documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/mf-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Nonlinear elastic-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening selected based on published Ti-6Al-4V stress-strain data. Model form justified by comparison of predicted vs. measured load-displacement curves showing capture of yield and post-yield behavior."
      },
      "rationale": "The nonlinear elastic-plastic model with isotropic hardening (Ramberg-Osgood fit to ASTM F136 coupon data) was selected as the appropriate constitutive form for Ti-6Al-4V under quasi-static loading. Model form is consistent with established literature for titanium alloy spinal implant simulation. The load-displacement curve shape, including yield transition, is reproduced within acceptance bounds. Gradation 3 achieved: model form justified with supporting literature and QoI-level comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/mi-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Material properties (E, yield stress, tangent modulus) sourced from lot-specific coupon testing of the same Ti-6Al-4V material lot used in the physical constructs. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of production screws."
      },
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (E = 114 GPa ± 2.1 GPa), yield stress (895 MPa ± 12 MPa), and tangent modulus (1.8 GPa) were obtained from tensile coupon testing of the same material lot as the test constructs. Screw geometry was characterized via coordinate measuring machine (CMM) on three production screws. Input uncertainty propagated through Monte Carlo sampling (n=500). Gradation 3 achieved: inputs traceable to lot-specific measurements with uncertainty quantified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/ts-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories; constructs assembled from production-representative screws and rods; sample size sufficient for statistical comparison per ASME V&V 40 guidance."
      },
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested: six at Laboratory A (FDA CDRH) and five at Laboratory B (DePuy Synthes). All constructs used production-representative hardware from the same manufacturing lot. Inter-laboratory variability was assessed and found to be within expected bounds (CV < 5% for stiffness). N=11 provides adequate statistical power for E/uval metric computation. Gradation 3 achieved: multi-laboratory testing with production-representative samples."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/tc-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Test conditions replicate ASTM F1717 standard fixture geometry and loading rate. Single load magnitude tested (monotonic to 40 mm displacement at 5 mm/min). Gradation 2 accepted given that the COU is specifically defined as ASTM F1717 standard test replication."
      },
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted strictly per ASTM F1717 protocol: fixed-fixed fixture, 5 mm/min quasi-static displacement rate, ambient temperature (23°C ± 2°C), in air. Only a single test condition (standard ASTM F1717) was evaluated — no variation in load level, rate, or environment. This limits the factor to Gradation 2. However, the COU is explicitly bounded to the ASTM F1717 standard condition, so this limitation is acknowledged and accepted as part of the COU definition. This factor is below the nominal required level of 3 but is accepted given COU scoping."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/eip-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) are demonstrated to be equivalent to the physical test configuration through documented traceability from CMM measurements, material certificates, and test fixture drawings."
      },
      "rationale": "Geometric equivalency confirmed by CMM measurement of three production screws compared to CAD nominal dimensions (max deviation 0.03 mm). Material property equivalency confirmed by lot-specific coupon testing. Boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture per fixture drawing review. Contact conditions (screw-rod, set screw torque) characterized and matched to experimental assembly protocol. Gradation 3 achieved: full traceability from physical test to model inputs documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
