      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/rqi-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the COU decision: stiffness characterizes construct rigidity relevant to fusion biomechanics; yield force and force at 40 mm characterize structural integrity under worst-case loading."
      },
      "rationale": "The three QoIs are the primary outputs required by ASTM F1717 and directly inform the regulatory decision on structural adequacy of the pedicle screw construct. Construct stiffness relates to load-sharing with the fusion mass. Yield force and force at 40 mm displacement bound the structural failure envelope. These QoIs are established in the literature as clinically relevant surrogates for in vivo performance. Gradation 3 achieved: QoI relevance to COU decision documented with clinical and regulatory justification."
    },
    {
