        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Validation activities (ASTM F1717 bench testing, N=11, two laboratories) are directly representative of the COU: same device geometry, same loading protocol, same material lot, same QoIs as the intended regulatory submission context."
      },
      "rationale": "The validation activities are directly congruent with the COU. The physical test configuration (ASTM F1717, non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw, production hardware) is identical to the intended use context. Multi-laboratory testing increases confidence in result generalizability. The FEA model is applied in the same configuration as the validation case. No extrapolation beyond the validated domain is required for the regulatory decision. Gradation 3 achieved: validation activities are directly representative of the COU with no significant gaps."
